## Old Reliable

We can use a standard `for` loop to look at every item. 

We start our counter `i` at `0` (because arrays start at Index 0!).
We want the loop to stop when `i` reaches the `.length` of the array.

```javascript
let heroes = ["Batman", "Superman", "Flash"];
// length is 3. We want i=0, i=1, and i=2. 
// So we say 'while i is less than length'.

for (let i = 0; i < heroes.length; i++) {
  console.log("Hello " + heroes[i]);
}
```

This prints: Hello Batman, Hello Superman, Hello Flash.

